text: CNEQ: Concentrated Risk With High Return Potential. The Alger Concentrated Equity ETF (CNEQ) offers exposure to 30 high-conviction, growth-oriented stocks, heavily weighted toward mega-cap technology and AI leaders. CNEQ has outperformed benchmark indices over the past year, driven by the AI growth theme and significant allocations to the Magnificent 7 stocks. Despite high concentration and sector risk, I recommend a Buy rating for CNEQ, best used as a satellite position to enhance technology exposure within a diversified portfolio.

text: Alexandria Real Estate: I'm Buying The Post-Earnings Plunge. Alexandria Real Estate (ARE) shares have plunged, creating a potential buying opportunity, as the stock appears deeply oversold after a capitulation-like selloff. ARE faces challenges including oversupply of lab space, weak biotech IPO market, and concerns over a possible dividend cut, but its payout ratio remains reasonable. The REIT offers a nearly 10% dividend yield, trades at a low valuation, and could benefit from future interest rate cuts and renewed biotech demand.

text: Gladstone Land Is Worth Biting Into, Owning A Piece Of Scarce Farmland. For my initial coverage of Gladstone Land Corp (LAND), I'm calling it a buy, in agreement with the Wall St and SA analyst consensus as of this writing. Key positives are steady monthly dividend payouts and modest 10 year dividend growth, as well as a diverse land portfolio across the US and trading below book value per share. This REIT is moving some leases to a participation-rent model rather than fixed rent, so that could also drive some uncertainty in revenue and earnings trends.
